Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored a brace to secure victory for England
Morten Hjulmand scored an equalizer for Denmark in the 34th minute
Jordan Pickford barely saw Hjulmand's goal coming
Post-Match Reflections: Kane said there will probably be loads of noise and a bit of disappointment back home
Southgate's men need to stay together and understand supporters' frustration
Danish midfielder Pierre-Emile Hojbjerg traded the man of the match award for three points
Miscellaneous Highlights: Prince of Wales and Denmark's King Frederik attended the game
England fans largely cleared out within a few minutes of the final whistle
The game was held at Deutsche Bank Park in Frankfurt, Germany
